init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States has to stop the Chinese military, but they are no match for Chinaâ€™s war machines.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The explosions are so large, they ignite the atmosphere.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American president felt bad about the civilian casualties, but felt that they were necessary to bring justice back to the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells the Chinese to disband and allow free elections.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They disagree, and everyone knows that they will use nuclear weapons to protect their power.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is finally at peace, but it will be a long time before America gets over the horror of what they had to do.
